A selection condition {{arxiv_2305_05403_FO0019||FO}} is a statement {{arxiv_2305_05403_FO0020||FO}}, where each component can either be instantiated, or a wildcard (``{{arxiv_2305_05403_FO0021||FO}}''). For example, {{arxiv_2305_05403_FO0022||FO}} is a selection condition. The result of a selection condition {{arxiv_2305_05403_FO0023||FO}} on a KB {{arxiv_2305_05403_FO0024||FO}} (written {{arxiv_2305_05403_FO0025||FO}}) is the set of all statements in {{arxiv_2305_05403_FO0026||FO}} that match {{arxiv_2305_05403_FO0027||FO}} at its non-wildcard positions. For example, {{arxiv_2305_05403_FO0028||FO}} selects all people born in Warsaw, and {{arxiv_2305_05403_FO0029||FO}} selects all awards won by Marie Curie.